<h1 id="configuring-git">Configuring git</h1>
<p>git config ‚Äìglobal user.email ‚Äúyour email‚Äù
git config ‚Äìglobal user.name ‚Äúyour name‚Äù</p>

<h1 id="for-adding-a-remote-github-definitiondestination">For adding a remote github definition/destination</h1>
<p>git remote add origin https://github.com/<Your Github="" userid="">/Blog.git</Your></p>

<p>git remote add origin https://github.com/nilskuhler/resumecard.git</p>

<p>git add .                                       # add all files in current folder to local repo
git add <folder>/*                              # for one folder
git add *                                       # for every thing</folder></p>

<p>git commit -m ‚Äú‚Äù                                # commit to local repo</p>

<p>git push -u origin master                       # commit to remote repo</p>

<p>git status</p>

<p>git ls-files *.md                               # list all *.md files in a local repository</p>

<p>git rm *.md                                     # remove all *.md files in a local repository</p>

<h1 id="in-case-you-want-to-update-your-remote-files-and-in-case-of-conflicts">In case you want to update your remote files and in case of conflicts</h1>
<h1 id="with-the-following-command-your-local-files-will-be-overruled-the-file-on-git">With the following command your local files will be overruled the file on git.</h1>
<p>git push -u origin master ‚Äìforce</p>

